<span id="freeTextContainer18299408010695006064"><strong>Excellent trauma-informed analysis of antiBlack racism &amp; healing</strong><br/><br/>This book was a great and informative read. I appreciated the approach of using trauma-informed practices to understand how racial healing is most likely only possible once everyone engages in the process of “clean pain” vs. “dirty pain.” </span>

